              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For a domain migration, Google typically recognises the move within 2-4 weeks when a Change of Address is submitted in Search Console. Full ranking recovery to pre-migration levels takes 2-6 months on average. Individual pages may be re-indexed within days; the aggregate authority transfer is slower.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do 301 redirects preserve all link equity during a migration?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A 301 redirect passes roughly 90-99% of link equity from the old URL to the new one. The equity transfer is real but not instantaneous — Google needs to crawl the redirect, recrawl the new URL, and update its index. Full equity consolidation can take 2-6 months.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the safest time to run a site migration?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
